Orchestrates load/save of a JSON task store and keeps its rendered markdown view in sync. All five entry points (`list`, `add_task`, `delete_task`, `render`, `migrate`) load from `paths.store`, apply mutations, and call `save()` to persist both the JSON and regenerated `docs/STATUS.md` in a single step — the view can never lag the store it was written from.

`load()` decodes JSON and backfills missing `id` fields for legacy rows; `save()` pretty-prints JSON with a trailing newline (git-diffable) and renders markdown via `render_markdown()`. Task ids are auto-assigned by max-existing + 1 in `add_task()`. `migrate()` is a one-time bootstrap from a source markdown table, guarded by `StoreNotEmpty` to prevent re-running. `delete_task()` rejects unknown ids; `render()` re-syncs the view after manual store edits. All I/O is abstracted through the `Fs` trait.